	<tr>
		<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
	
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			Ok people, let me inform you of a very important fact about this spell. You DO NOT have to be in melee range of your intended target to cast this spell.  I've found the best way to use this spell is to first cast O'keil's Radiation on your tank let him melee two creatures to get them &quot;mad&quot; at only him and then target the tank from a DISTANCE, and cast this spell.  The range of this spell is close to that of Icestrike.  Try this and you will appreciate this spell more than if you use it when your intended targets are directly around you.  If you want a spell to hurt those things around then use Fingers of Fire.  Again, this is a Ranged AE spell, Not a Point Blank AE spell like Fingers of Fire or Numbing Cold.
			</font>
	
		</td>
	</tr>
	
